# Cloudflare CLI/API credentials — TEMPLATE.
# Copy to `.cloudflare.env` (gitignored) and fill in the values THERE.
# Do NOT put real tokens in this committed example, and do NOT paste them into chat.
#
# Create a SCOPED API token: Cloudflare dashboard → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token → Custom.
#   • Now (Worker config only):     Account › Workers Scripts : Edit
#                                   Account › Account Settings : Read   (to read the account id)
#   • Later, at cutover (apex + www→apex redirect), add for the opendream.co.th zone:
#                                   Zone › DNS : Edit
#                                   Zone › Config Rules : Edit   (Single Redirect rules)
#   Set a short expiry; revoke the token when finished.
#
# Account ID is shown in the dashboard sidebar / Workers overview.
# Zone ID is on the opendream.co.th zone Overview page (only needed at cutover).

CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
CLOUDFLARE_ZONE_ID=
